      "content": "It is possible that nausea and hand tremors are side effects as your body adjusts to lithium. However, because lithium can affect various bodily functions, you should contact your prescribing doctor soon to discuss these symptoms. They can determine if this is a normal adjustment effect or if a dosage adjustment or further monitoring is needed for you.",
