      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While staying very well-hydrated is crucial when taking lithium to prevent toxicity, drastically increasing water intake alone may not resolve nausea or tremors. It's important to understand that dehydration can actually increase the risk of lithium side effects, so follow your doctor's advice on fluid intake. Since you can't see them right away, you should contact their office for advice on managing these symptoms over the phone before making major changes.",
      "source": "target",
